text: Listened to this after the first time I kissed a girl

Cannot be overstated how worse the Internet is now than in 2000 in basically all aspects. Yandex only usable search engine. Modern website design looks like chromium metallic diarrhea to appeal to the masses. Bloated chatbots clog traffic. Bloglike hypertextuality no longer used.

You just have to look at some old blogs or forums from 1999, 2003, 2006, etc. Sharp stimulating design, clarity, everything functional and intuitive, encourages exploration and venturing out the zone. Now it's a factory rail. Email is more futuristic than anything made post-2010.

Just the corporation's logo and motto stylized in font, simple colors, appearing for ~2 seconds total on the screen, specific products not even mentioned or shown. The George Bush "bureaucRATS" campaign ad with all the useless clutter removed, very reduced. Never above 5 seconds.

I have already speculated that advertisements in general are probably mostly useless. I think good ads would basically be like the Neon Genesis Evangelion title cards and Outlast Morphogenic Engine hallucinations. Brutal design fragments flashing for a few seconds to leave a mark
